  "body": "**What happened**:\r\n\r\nRecently we found that kube-apiserver will leak goruntine in large-scale scene with lots of 504 response code, and lots of logs like `Throttling request took %v, request: %s:%s`\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nFix the goruntine leak.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nSet-up a large-scale Kubernetes cluster, or the following codes may help you how the goruntine leaks:\r\n\r\n* The root cause of the problem is at [k8s.io/client-go/rest/request.go#L806](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/staging/src/k8s.io/client-go/rest/request.go#L806):\r\n```go\r\nfunc (r *Request) Do() Result {\r\n\tr.tryThrottle()\r\n \t\r\n\t...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n* Reproduce it:\r\n```go\r\nvar (\r\n\tleak int32 = 0\r\n)\r\n\r\nfunc getAsync(client rest.Interface) (interface{}, error) {\r\n\tctx, cancelFn := context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), time.Second*5)\r\n\tdefer cancelFn()\r\n\r\n\tresultCh := make(chan interface{}, 1)\r\n\tdefer close(resultCh)\r\n\r\n\tgo func() {\r\n\t\tatomic.AddInt32(&leak, 1)\r\n\t\tresultCh <- client.\r\n\t\t\tGet().Context(ctx).Timeout(time.Second * 5).\r\n\t\t\tResource(\"pods\").Namespace(\"default\").Name(\"foo\").\r\n\t\t\tDo()\r\n\t\tatomic.AddInt32(&leak, -1)\r\n\t}()\r\n\r\n\tselect {\r\n\tcase <-ctx.Done():\r\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"timeout\")\r\n\tcase result := <-resultCh:\r\n\t\treturn result, nil\r\n\t}\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\t// if you want to run this main function, please set master and kubeconfig value.\r\n\tconfig, err := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(master, kubeconfig)\r\n\r\n\tif nil != err {\r\n\t\tpanic(err)\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\t// set QPS to a very low value, reproduce large-scale scenes\r\n\tconfig.QPS = 0.000001\r\n\tconfig.Burst = 1\r\n\r\n\tif nil != err {\r\n\t\tpanic(fmt.Errorf(\"failed to init client, err: %v\", err))\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tc, err := kubernetes.NewForConfig(config)\r\n\tif nil != err {\r\n\t\tpanic(fmt.Errorf(\"failed to init client, err: %v\\n\", err))\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\twait := sync.WaitGroup{}\r\n\r\n\tfor i := 0; i < 1000; i++ {\r\n\t\twait.Add(1)\r\n\t\tgo func() {\r\n\t\t\tgetAsync(c.RESTClient())\r\n\t\t\twait.Done()\r\n\t\t}()\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\twait.Wait()\r\n\r\n\tfmt.Printf(\"goruntine leak num: %v\", leak)\r\n}\r\n\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\nNothing yet.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n\r\nNever mind, the latest version of Kubernetes also has this issue.",
